        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 26 at 1:23PM MDT by NWS Missoula MT</headline>
        <description>At 122 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Silver Bow, or near Butte, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph. Heavy rainfall.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Butte, Silver Bow, Walkerville, Ramsay, Newcomb, and Nissler.

This includes Interstate 90 between mile markers 213 and 229.
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead
to localized flooding in uptown Butte. Do not drive your vehicle
through flooded roadways.</instruction>
